    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-01-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="107"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/525.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Italian Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-01-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to my informal communication of
                    the 9th instant,<note n="1" xml:id="d107fn1">Not printed.</note> regarding the
                    Joint Opium Commission, which is shortly to meet at Shanghai, I have the honor
                    to inform you that this Government has consulted the various powers
                    participating in the coming conference, and I am now happy to be able to invite
                    your Government to delegate representatives who will take part in the
                    deliberations, which it is hoped will result in restricting, and be instrumental
                    in the final suppression of, the opium evil.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
